reviewText: Self-absorbed and un-professional production. Script reads like a teen-age novella.  Best acting is by the lead female

I first read about walk-ins from one of Ruth Montgomery's books, then watching Ghost Whisperer, then Drop Dead Diva. Even after being familiar with the concept, I still am undecided about it. That aside, this movie wasn't too cohesive. Some things just didn't make sense. I also didn't see the humor in the film as described (well, I did fall asleep on it, but the parts that I did see didn't have any humor and the subject was death).
